rComments: Silvija is a great prof! The content in the course is all very applicable to everyday life, and you will learn a lot! Watching lectures is a must, since she sometimes says things that aren't on the slides (but she will test you on this). You definitely have time to put in the time and effort to read the book and attend lecs to do well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: This is a great bird course for life science students. Course content was straight forward, and the professor just reads off of the slides, so there is no need to watch lectures.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Her lectures are not important at all. Her midterm and finals have questions come from the lecture slides, textbook and supplementary material and they would ask the most detailed thing. Course is easy if you can sit and memorize 6 sets of slides for the midterm and another 6 for the final. She also tends to go off topic quite easily. Nice lady tho
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Test heavy']

rComments: This course is intense, not a bird course by no means. Unless you dedicated over 30 hours a week memorizing, you won't do well.

i love silvja shes so funny - not in a haha way but her accent is just thick enough to alter how she says words and her spelling isnt the best - its very cute. good course and actually enjoyed it, which i didnt expect.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Accessible outside class', 'Caring']

rComments: Easy 4.0, read & watch the lectures.

The content was easy to understand, but her lecture style wasn't the best. I found that she repeated herself A LOT, making it harder to stay focused while using WebOption. Most of the lectures had the exact same content as the textbook. If you're looking for an easy pass- take it. As long as you read the textbook/discussions, you'll be fine.

Great at explaining content. The exams (50 midterm /50 final) are everything she says in class and the supplementary materials. The TAs also do a great job at asking specific questions to get you to understand the material. There are no surprises on the exams. Professor Stefanovic is one of UTSC's best instructors. If you put in the work expect 4.0
One of the best profs I had at UTSC! Genuinely cares about her students and very approachable. Study hard for exams though!

Professor Stefanovic is an amazing professor. If you are genuinely interested in the course then definitely take it because you will benefit a lot. Professor Stefanovic is one of the nicest professors you will come across, especially if you go into office hours you will realize this. Very knowledgeable also.

If you are thinking to take EESA10 with her to boost your grades like I did, just don't. I got B from the course, she wasn't particularly interesting in lectures, you'll get around 70-80 in vague assignments regardless how perfect your writing is, in the end you'll be feeling like why you paid that money for a daft course you learnt nothing from.
I did not like this class. The assignments were killer. Stay away!
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: No Better way to describe  this class other than horrible. The marking criteria was all over the place, she included questions on the exam that were not covered in lecture or the readings. Compared my assignments to my classmates, some of us received 100% while others got 50% for the exact same work and calculations. Deserves less than a 1.

textbook is  hard to read due to too many terminology (I am in computer science), term test has many questions that are not covered in book nor lecture, and when you ask her, she thinks its obvious and need not be mentioned (I guess maybe if you are in chem then its common sense) she made mistake in term test marking and didn't want to change

I recommend this class if you are genuinely interested in how the human body and environment are connected. Moving on from the common forms of just climate change but more specific aspects of disease and biological hazards. The midterm and final are based on the firstlast 6 weeks of lectures and is all memorization. Assignments are mark boosters.

Don't take this course as a bird course, it's definitely not easy. TA's are disorganized, some give high marks on the assignment, others not so much which is unfair. Too many specific details are tested on the exam.

A really easy going professor. Some people may have a problem with her accent, but it's tolerable. Lecture and lecture notes are straight forward and simple. Assignments are fairly easy and will not take a long time to complete. Readings are not mandatory and exams were fair. Very easy to do well in this course
All necessary info included in lectures.  Textbook unnecessary.  Exams were all multi choice, but questions were poorly written and were repetitive.  Nice lady.
Great Prof! she is awesome,..i didnt know her much in EESA10 cuz it was a huge class...but after taking this course I changed my mind about her!
Useless TA's,Unorganized Notes, Incomprehensible Prof, Google taught me more than she did. Not a bird course

She is an extremely nice prof. The lectures are simple and pretty easy. The readings in the book aren't that important since most of the important information is in the lectures. The exams are extremely fair. If you attend the lectures and study, you can easily get an A

She is not a bad prof. She just has problems with her accent. She's actually very helpful and approacable. U don't have to read the text. Just attend lectures and take some notes to supplement her slide notes. Her exams were mainly M/C but extremely fair, she asks lots of questions so the individual questions aren't worth a lot. Can easily do well.

Her accent is tolerable. Not really a bird course; workload is just low. Pure memorizing for tests. Pay close attention to details when studying. Best to retype her notes - somewhat disorganized and lack flow & lots of errors. Recognize defs from her text as she'll ask questions about them. Check your ans with TAs before you hand in your assigns.

I think she should really work on her wordings. Spelling and grammar mistakes are everywhere in her slides and even EXAM. She asks random stats on exams. Slow lecture. Sweet lady. Absoultely useless TAs. This is one of those courses that are supposed to be easy but marked hard. Annoying course.

She's a very sweet woman and is always open to questions during lectures. The course itself is very easy. She even says at the beginning of the year that this course is easy. The 2 assignments were a cinch. The midterm and final exam are basically pure memorization but a good amount of the questions are things she says in class (not on notes).

Teaches like ur in kindergarden. Strong accent & spelling mistakes on assign, lecs & exams. TA's R useless & tough markers whn assign is supposed 2 B easy. Speaks really slow. Doesn't seem like University prof but instd Elementary teacher. However, easy crse & very friendly. She lectures the obvious so it's like common sense.
Terrible professor that neglected the needs of the students and hired useless TA's that marked assignments unfairly and gave marks that was not reflective of the marking scheme.

She is funny. Her slides are helpful. Its a course w/ a whole bunch of random info, alot which u will find useful & applicable. Easy assign., easy midterm, confusing final.. O-kay prof although sometimes I wish she would talk faster and explain more.
very slow lectures.  should prepare her notes before class instead of trying to remember her ideas.
